dcterms:description: The flight records including delay information provided by the United States Department of Transportation, containing important information such as Departure/Arrival Airport, Scheduled Departure/Arrival Time, Actual Departure/Arrival Time, and Airlines.

dcterms:creator: C. L. Scovel III
I. General
dcterms:description: Trajectory data collected continuously by automatic dependent surveillance-broadcast (ADS-B), which includes Aircraft Identifications, position information (Longitude, Latitude, Altitude), flight status, and aircraft attributes.
dcterms:title: Trajectory data

dcterms:description: Data from air route traffic control centers (ARTCCs) which includes information about staffing and controller training time.
dcterms:title: ATC data

dcterms:description: Weather condition data gathered from the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA), including temperature, precipitation, humidity, sky conditions, wind speed, and wind direction.
dcterms:title: Weather data

dcterms:description: Data from ADS-B Exchange, which includes all flights installed with ADS-B equipment, covering most commercial aviation with fields such as Aircraft Identifications, position information, flight status, and aircraft attributes.
dcterms:title: ADS-B data
